&quot;Apologist&quot; means someone who argues on behalf of people who are wrong, not someone who apologizes.  It isn't neccesarily a negative term, it just means that the person being defended is not generally highly regarded.  For example, if I were to argue that Kaiser Wilhelm II was actually an intelligent person who got unlucky, someone (usually who disagrees) would call me a Kaiser Wilhelm apologist.<br>
<br>
Seriously, Agrul, the last 5 levels in the game, all hell levels.   <br>
<br>
If you are supposed to be maximally hostile by every means neccesary, shouldn't you be using 3rd party software that can't be detected and fabricating complaints to GMs to try to get the other guilds disbanded?  It's war after all.  <br>
<br>
If not, then you've chosen an arbitrary line of &quot;shitiness&quot; that you won't cross.  And since that line is arbitrary, why not set it at a less irritating place?<br>
<br>
There's no sense in defending something that you personally would not do.  Would you do this?<br>
<br>
