<br>
The source of this whole well of pissed off people is just the difference between the people who are playing to make friends and the people who are playing to win.<br>
<br>
I play to win.  If I can make friends in the process, so much the better, but I don't believe in giving the opponet a break just to make them like me.  So while I hope Nafgar dies and gets corpsecamped back to level 5, I merely hate him because he's my opponet, not because I disagree with his style or think he should physically die in real life.<br>
<br>
Pino's sleeping disorder is unfortunate, but it's hardly fair to ask people to give him a break in a game because of it.  If Larry Bird returned to basketball, you couldn't tell people not to steal the ball from him just because he's not as fast as he used to be.<br>
<br>
(You could make an argument that you should be nice to people so that they give you breaks later, thus helping you win, but that's only if you expect to need more breaks then them.  I don't need breaks, so I don't give em.)<br>
