<br>
To set the record straight, I was there when this all happened and was involved in training DBC off Pino.<br>
I know this server has no rules and that's fine.<br>
Pino didn't whine or complain at all, and that's great.<br>
<br>
Regarding the checkmate argument and chess, that isn't applicable due to the fact that when the game ends, it's over for good. Chess is not persistent. EQ is. If you pwn someone in chess, you can shake hands, bitch slap the guy, whatever but the game is over forever and in the past.<br>
<br>
We all want to score points and be in the top spot on this server but I'm sure everyone wants to have fun playing this game. What is the point of playing and being the number one in points if you hate the game itself?<br>
<br>
I don't care if I get CC'd, trained, bind rushed, whatever. That stuff is part of Sullon Zek.<br>
<br>
When some idiots decide to bind camp someone who is AFK, it makes me wonder exactly what is going through their minds. Is it:<br>
<br>
&quot;Wow, we're going to score some serious points here with no work whatsoever&quot;?<br>
<br>
or perhaps:<br>
<br>
&quot;Let's delevel this guy so next time we see him he is a weaker foe&quot;<br>
<br>
or maybe even:<br>
<br>
&quot;Let's piss this guy off so much that he quits. One less enemy.&quot;<br>
<br>
Regardless, they are all acts of cowardice and take no skill whatsoever. OK, so one enemy got a bit weaker this day. Pin a rose on your nose. I love PvP and enjoy the challenge. Bind camping an AFK is NOT PvP. I truly feel sorry for someone who feels better about himself/herself because he ganked a guy down 5 levels when he was AFK.<br>
<br>
Many people on these boards say there is no place for honor on SZ but I believe there is. I have had many bloody fights with people from TDC, Zanshin (before disbanding), Sanctus Lumen, and even DBC (Well, one anyway: Marqus) where their members were very honorable in the aftermath no matter what the casualties were on both sides. Does this make me soft against these guys? No way! I'm going to come with all the artillery I've got every time we meet.<br>
<br>
This post will probably draw loads of flames from people who will mock my honor but that's ok. In closing, before last night I had never even seen Pino but I felt obligated, as an enemy of DBC, to do something about it. That's all I have to say.<br>
<br>
Zhugruk<br>
