<br>
If you aren't playing by the rules, then you aren't playing the game.  I do my best to stay within the rules because when I win a game, I like to know it was because I kick ass (or perhaps because my opponet did something stupid).  When I find out where you were hiding, it's because I know the territory and knew where the good hiding places were, not because some external program told me.<br>
<br>
Any fool can cheat and win.  And what's the point of being the #1 fool when you can be the #1 skilled player?<br>
<br>
I'd rather be a winner in my head and a loser at the game than the other way around.  Until I can beat someone on a level playing field, I haven't beat them at all.  I think that's the attitude you'll get from most &quot;real gamers&quot;.  Other people literally only want to win, and will break rules to get that sense of winning, but that's just their own eggshell thin ego talking.<br>
<br>
(In poker you might cheat cause there's a hundred bucks on the table.  In online games, there's no reason other than your own overinflated ego or small, yappy dog like desire to impress others.)<br>
<br>
PS:<br>
I didn't like the Prophets because they cheated.  If VZ were hard coded, I still wouldn't like them, because it wouldn't change the fact that they were known for breaking rules.<br>
<br>
Perhaps if they came to Sullon, I would wipe the slate clean, but given their bannings for being caught using external programs to cheat with, I doubt they'd deserve it.  People who cheat tend to stick to their methods, they'd simply find new ways to cheat here.<br>
<br>
I should probably mention that this is all the &quot;theory&quot; behind my gaming style.  Even the most dedicated rule abiding football player may get furious enough to kick another player in the nuts, which is definiately against the rules, but while spurious outbursts may be forgivable, people who commit a sort of &quot;1st degree cheating&quot; are generally just fools, too incompetent to win on their own, and not really worth my time because they're too far below my skill level to even have a good conversation with.<br>
