There's no defined goals for winning.<br>
<br>
If winning = killing people, then bind camping someone is legit.  You'd be a fool not to.<br>
<br>
If winning = being highest level, ditto.<br>
<br>
If winning = proving your skill in 1 on 1 fights with a level playing field, then bind camping someone is as pointless as farming greens.<br>
<br>
If winning = having lots of friends, including enemies, then bind camping anyone is counter-productive.<br>
<br>
Since EQ has no real point, various people are going by various and contradictory definitions of winning.  You say we lost, we say we won, over the same event.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
This is why I can't wait til Shadowbane.<br>
