we play the server as a war with no limits, thats why we came here. if we wanted a watered down pvp server with 56 ress'es at the end for everyone and hand holding and a pat on the back from the adversary we would have stayed on rallos with our uber equipped 55 - 60 chars and continued to PK there rather then build all new ones. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/bsullonzektavern.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=minidas>Minidas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/4/01 6:40:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3914.topic&index=155>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: IE Defeats DB &amp; TDC, Ruin monk comments on PvP and D</span><hr size=1> It's actually the least stupid war analogy yet propsed here to my knowledge.  WWII was essentially a total war with no limits.  The constraints were practical ones; no poison gas because of retaliation/common decency.  Little shooting of parachuting pilots because of retaliation/common decency.<br>
<br>
Real fighter pilots, with their lives on the line, DIDN'T shoot them by and large.  It would have made the war a lot less pleasant in a hurry and been personally distasteful.<br>
<br>
The arguement that the SZ ruleset allows for and encourages all behavior is specious.  It seems compelling on the face of it, but it doesn't actually hold up.  A genuinely total effort that disregards &quot;moral&quot; inhibitions about things like bindcamping afks would also disregard minor matters like immo healing on VZ.  It isn't honourable, but we're playing to win, goddamn it? <br>
<br>
The rules of SZ are simple a bare boned, negative framework.  This in no way suggests that players are somehow being &quot;cool&quot; by behaving their most bestial. I wasn't just throwing the word around when I said the DB charter was &quot;fascisty.&quot;  If you've read enough fascist &quot;intellectual treatises&quot; you get a feel for what they read like.  I've actually taken a course specifically on fascism, and this sort of irrationalist sense that we should throw aside outdated morals now that we realize we can is part and parcel.  Rules, morals are constraints of the weak and we should realize our will to power.<br>
<br>
But it's fundamentally unsound.  Just because the msot fundamental rules are negative (only forbidding behavior, not telling us how we should behave otherwise) doesn't mean that positive rules _should_ not exist in addition.  Even though VZ should be hardcoded, purists ARE cool by their enforcement of a rule that improves the server.<br>
<br>
So would people who realized the ability to act like an ass isn't a reason to do so.<br>
<br>
